---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">ðŸš€ Hosting Astro on GitHub Pages</h1>

  <p class="mb-4">This guide walks you through deploying your Astro site to GitHub Pages using static site generation (SSG).</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Step 1: Configure <code>astro.config.mjs</code></h2>
  <pre class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-auto">
import { defineConfig } from "astro/config";
import tailwind from "@tailwindcss/vite";
import { githubPages } from "@astrojs/github";

export default defineConfig({
  output: "static",
  vite: {
    plugins: [tailwind()],
  },
  integrations: [githubPages()],
});
  </pre>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Step 2: Build the site</h2>
  <pre class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-auto">
npm run build
  </pre>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Step 3: Push to GitHub</h2>
  <pre class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-auto">
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/your-repo.git
git checkout -b gh-pages
git add dist -f
git commit -m "Deploy Astro site"
git subtree push --prefix dist origin gh-pages
  </pre>

  <p class="mt-6">ðŸ”’ Donâ€™t forget to enable GitHub Pages in the repo settings and point it to the <code>gh-pages</code> branch!</p>
</BaseLayout>

